Weekly Plex Media Server database maintenance using DBRepair
(https://github.com/ChuckPa/DBRepair).

Checks for active streams before proceeding. If any are detected,
sends a yellow "Skipped" Discord embed and exits. Otherwise downloads
the latest DBRepair from GitHub, copies it into the Plex Docker
container, and runs an automatic Stop > Check > Repair > Reindex >
Start cycle.

Logs:
  Host:      /mnt/cache/appdata/PlexMediaServer/dbrepair_schedule.log
  Container: /config/DBRepair.log

Discord embeds:
  green  = success
  yellow = skipped (active streams)
  red    = error

Configuration values are baked into the top of this script at deploy
time by deploy.ps1 in the repo, which reads a local .secrets file and
writes the result here over SMB. Edit .secrets and rerun deploy.ps1
to change settings — do NOT edit this script in-place via the User
Scripts UI, as the next deploy will overwrite your edits.

Recommended schedule: Weekly, low-traffic window
(e.g. 0 3 * * 0 for Sunday 3am).
